HEADWORD: Uranous
<hw>U"ra*nous</hw> <pr>(⟦umac⟧"r⟦adot⟧*n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or containing, uranium;
designating those compounds in which uranium has a lower valence as
contrasted with the <contr>uranic</contr> compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

